						<summary>

						<p>The top and the bottom of the stone are both built in. This records some provision made for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mahādēvar Tiruppanaṅgāḍ-Uḍaiyār at Perumpālaiyūr in Perumpālaiyūr-nāḍu, a sub-division of Ūṛṛukkāṭṭu-kōṭṭam, by <hi rend="bold">Kāḍavi [daughter of] Tiruppālaiyūr-Kiḻavaṉ</hi> a resident of the village.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
